Alfred TRICE, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES. No. 8693. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 7, 1938. Russell Graham, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Ben Harrison, U., S'. Atty., of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee,

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
